name: Five career bundle
description: Collection - Five career bundle - five_career_bundle_0001

name: Mask of the Shadow-Slayer
description: Garb worn by the Shades of the Ashen Hills, whose footfalls leave no sound, and whose blades slice through armour as cleanly as skin.

name: Purist's Stovepipe
description: Note how the ears are muffled, so the righteous seeker be not distracted by his quarry's perfidious lies...

name: Incandescent Brand
description: Borne by only the most adept at the pyromantic arts, it is said to reflect purity of the devotion to Aqshy.

name: Memento Furioso
description: One simply cannot meet the eyes of this death mask without experiencing foreknowledge of a fiery, fiery death.

name: Fulminator's Crown
description: Metal is said to dampen a wizard's connection to the Winds of Magic, so only a truly accomplished pyromancer can wear such a crown.

name: The Golden Taurox
description: Tauroxes are stubborn, belligerent and almost impossible to stop once they get going. Remind you of anyone?

name: The Anvil of Doom
description: Despite being named for an ancient dawi war machine, we don't recommend hitting this with a hammer ... unless you're well out of the wearer's reach.

name: The Iron Mohawk
description: Beset by shameful baldness? Unable to dye your locks to a brilliant, death-defying orange? Never fear. A few nails, and you'll be as fearsome a slayer as ever there was.

name: Trophy of the Gave
description: Proof that the wearer has survived (indeed, flourished) in battle with the forest-lurking beastmen. Smells horrible.

name: Marienburg Bicorne
description: Marienburg has a poor reputation as a nest of pirates and ne'er do wells. A reputation well-earned. Who knows how many times this hat was stolen from previous owners.

name: Scour-Sun Helm
description: The Knights of Blazing Sun hold that nothing evil nor corrupt can endure beneath the sun's gaze. Well, not for long.

name: Stolen Swine
description: We're not really sure about this one, to be honest. Is it Victor's assistant? His lunch? A familiar sent by Sigmar to embody his fulminating rage? No one's dared ask. Much less tried to take it off him.

name: Deathvigil Mask
description: So rumour goes, Deathvigil Hunters are a secret sect belonging to the Order of the Silver Hammer, dirtying their hands with tasks too burdensome for even the witch hunters.

name: Aspect of Adanhu
description: A mummer's mask, worn at festivals to recount the legends of Athel Loren. Embodies nobility, wisdom and sacrifice.

name: Executioner's Helm
description: Mask worn by those steeped in the mysteries of Khaine. Denotes an individual best kept at arms length, and never out of sight.

name: Wildrunner's Helm
description: Helm once belong to a knight of Avelorn, having met unfortunate end in the Everqueen's service. His whispers still echo through the steel.

name: Naggarond Backstabber
description: Assassin's garb, worn by the particularly untrustworthy (distinctions matter in Naggaroth).

name: Marshal Ludenwald's Favourite Hat
description: Last seen in the vaults of the Emperor Karl-Franz himself. Kruber swears he doesn't know how it ended up in his quarters.

name: Hellequin's Raiment
description: Showy (if tattered) soldier's garb, commissioned from Guisaume of Parravon by an unknown mercenary captain.

name: Friedhelm's Flamboyance
description: Apparently the feathers are magical, though who made it so - and for what purpose - have long been lost to the mists of time.

name: Gambler's Glamour
description: A beautifully-cut suit of rich cloth, designed to dazzle. No doubt purchased with crooked coin.

name: Gungasti
description: Redoubtable helm, named for the rare dwarfen musical instrument to which its horns owe strange similarity.

name: Valaya's Hearthguard
description: Gilded armour of a dawi ironbreaker who stands ever ready to defend his hearth and home.

name: Candlevane Collar
description: Somehow, these candles don't melt when the wizard is at her work. Probably best not to wonder what they're made of.

name: Judge of Myrmidia
description: Cross not Myrmidia's judges, for their verdict is seldom favourable, and their sentence always involves fire.

name: Agent of Malekith
description: Cloak yourself in the shadows and seek out the Witch-King's foes ... or just kill lots of Pactsworn for the fun of it. They make such pretty noises when they die.

name: Flamboyant Sellsword
description: There's no shame in being a mercenary. In fact, why not display a little bit of every uniform you've ever worn? Might remind some folk that you're on their side.

name: Dashing Rouge
description: Never let it be said that you're not one to strut your stuff, should the situation call for it. Derring-do? Optional. Rakish wist? Something of a work in progress.

name: Karak Norn Hold-Keeper
description: Take up your runic armour and stand firm against those who'd despoil your hearth and home. A rousing song wouldn't hurt neither, dawri.

name: Light of Judgement
description: So much injustice in the world. So much intolerance. Well, it's time to light a candle or two in Myrmidia's name and burn the injust and intolerant to ash, darlings.

name: Lohner's Collections
description: Multi-character collection

name: Molten Motley
description: Garb fit for the most magmatic of magicians. Unleash the fury of Aqshy in inimitable style.

name: Ellyrian Handmaiden
description: Don the garb of a temple handmaiden of Ellyrian; stern, austere and unflinching before those who would threaten Ulthuan.

name: Acolyte of Sea & Storm
description: Though the shipwreck drowned your companions, Sigmar has saved you for a higher purpose - one steeped in skaven blood.

name: Taal's Huntsman
description: Embrace your inner beast and roam the Stirland wilderness as a champion of King Taal.

name: Long Drong's Landlubber
description: It's time to set sail for plunder with the famed slayer pirates. Or it would be, if there was any sign of their ship.

name: Lohner's Brauzeit Collection
description: Multi-character collection

name: Wild Heath Warden
description: Sentinel of Athel Loren's wild border, where ancient waystones contain the wrath of hungry trees.

name: Elithis Pilgrimage
description: Vestments of a Witch Hunter determined to seek out heretics in distant lands. No word of his success (or failure) has ever reached the Empire.

name: Templar Herald
description: Armour of a knight charged with carrying Sigmar's message into the distant crusading lands of Araby. Judging by its condition, he was not well received.

name: Molten Soul
description: Ensorcelled raiment of a wizard determined to walk the weave of Aqshy. Mostly fireproof, though the same cannot alas be said of the wearer.

name: Vargza
description: Garb of a dispossessed king, doomed to wander the Worlds Edge Mountain in search of a home he can never reclaim.

name: Huntsmarshal's Raiment
description: When wandering the wilds, one should do so in style ... and wearing the odd trophy doesn't hurt.

name: Robes of the Illuminator
description: Mariah Holsrieke was famed for bringing light to challenging subjects both philosophical and physical ... many of which burned to ash beneath her scrutiny.

name: Defender of the Eight Peaks
description: Hofni Haraldson defended Karak Eight Peaks to his last breath. There are heroes, even in the dark.

name: Phoenix King's Bodyguard
description: Garb of Alvani Silestta, a Chracian White Lion tasked with protecting the ruler of Ulthuan in life or through death.

name: Sigmar's Prophet
description: Tattered rags once belonging to Gerhardt Wulf, the self-proclaimed Prophet of Sigmar. Welcome on the battlefield, less so in more civilised climes.

name: Wanderers in the Wild Collection
description: Clad your favorite hero in the garb of a seasoned traveller. The Wanderers in the Wild collection contains 10 premium cosmetics - one skin and one hat for each playable hero - inspired by forebears who forsook their homes for adventure in distant lands.

name: Unsung Heroes Collection
description: Grab yourself a new set of armour and honour the Unsung Heroes of the world.  The Unsung Heroes Collection contains 10 premium cosmetics - one skin and one hat for each playable hero - inspired by heroes whose feats deserve to be heard.
